Question: How do I do laundry at duke?
Response:
Answer: Laundry machines are available in designated laundry rooms located throughout all Duke residence halls. For many students, these machines are DukeCard and coin-operated, allowing for payment using either method. However, some residence halls, particularly those for first-year students, offer free laundry services. This service is managed by Duke Vending. If you encounter a broken machine or require reimbursement due to lost money, you should contact Duke Vending directly at 919-684-8363. Additionally, your HRL Campus Office can assist you in reaching out to Duke Vending for machine repairs. For any other issues related to the laundry facilities, you can call the East Campus Office at 919-684-5320 or contact your HRL Campus Office.

Sources:
1. https://students.duke.edu/living/housing/first-year-housing/what-to-expect-in-residence-halls/
2. https://students.duke.edu/living/housing/upperclass-housing/new-to-duke/
3. https://students.duke.edu/living/housing/amenities-services/

To report broken machines or to request reimbursement when money is lost in the machines, call Duke Vending at 684-8363.
